Phylogenetic analysis of 18S rRNA revealed that the sequences obtained in the present study belonged to C. parvum and C. bovis (Fig. 2
). Although it was not possible to differentiate between C. bovis and C. ryanae using PCR based on 18S rRNA, phylogenetic analysis was used to successfully differentiate between the species. In addition, phylogenetic analysis of hsp70 yielded the same results as those obtained by analyzing 18S rRNA (Fig. 3
).
